    """Improved version of `equation_v1`.

    Calculates acceleration for a nonlinear harmonic oscillator given position (x0) and velocity (x1).

    This version includes:
    - Polynomial terms up to cubic order in position and velocity.
    - Sinusoidal restoring force term to model nonlinear springs.
    - Linear and nonlinear damping/friction terms dependent on velocity.
    - Sign function term to model dry friction or Coulomb friction.

    Parameters:
    - x0 (np.ndarray): Position at time t.
    - x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity at time t.
    - params (np.ndarray): Array of parameters with length at least 12.

