    - Mixed coupling terms between position and velocity powers
    - Parametric excitation via sine/cosine functions of position/velocity
    - Exponential velocity-dependent damping-like term
    - Sign-sensitive quadratic velocity dependent damping

    Parameters:
        x0 (np.ndarray): Position at time t.
        x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity at time t.
        params (np.ndarray): Array of 12 parameters.

            params indices mapping:
            p[0]  = linear stiffness coefficient (-k)
            p[1]  = linear damping coefficient (-c)
            p[2]  = cubic stiffness coefficient (Duffing nonlinearity)
            p[3]  = quadratic velocity dependent coefficient
            p[4]  = cubic velocity dependent coefficient
            p[5]  = mixed linear position * linear velocity coupling coefficient
            p[6]  = quadratic position nonlinearity coefficient
            p[7]  = parametric forcing amplitude via sine(position)
            p[8]  = parametric forcing amplitude via cosine(velocity)
            p[9]  = mixed quadratic position * linear velocity term coefficient
            p[10] = mixed linear position * quadratic velocity term coefficient
            p[11] = exponential nonlinear damping amplitude

    Returns:
        np.ndarray: Calculated acceleration.
