    Improvements over equation_v1:
    - Replace discontinuous sign function with smooth tanh approximation for better numerical stability.
    - Maintain all nonlinear stiffness and damping terms.
    - Keep periodic forcing terms dependent on position and velocity.
    - Keep mixed nonlinear coupling term.
    - Maintain velocity-dependent exponential damping term with smooth sign approximation.

    Parameters:
        x0 (np.ndarray): Position at time t.
        x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity at time t.
        params (np.ndarray): Array of 12 parameters controlling various terms.

            params indices mapping:
            p[0]  = linear stiffness coefficient (-k)
            p[1]  = linear damping coefficient (-c)
            p[2]  = cubic stiffness coefficient (Duffing nonlinearity)
            p[3]  = quadratic velocity damping coefficient
            p[4]  = cubic velocity damping coefficient
            p[5]  = cross term coefficient between position and velocity
            p[6]  = sine(position) parametric forcing amplitude
            p[7]  = cosine(position) parametric forcing amplitude
            p[8]  = sine(velocity) parametric forcing amplitude
            p[9]  = cosine(velocity) parametric forcing amplitude
            p[10] = quadratic position nonlinearity coefficient
            p[11] = smooth exponential velocity-dependent damping-like term coefficient

    Returns:
        np.ndarray: Calculated acceleration y.
